From: virglrenderer patch <virglrenderer@patch>
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] virgl_video: support non-Mesa VA-API drivers (Intel xe/iHD, NVIDIA, etc.)

Remove the Mesa-only guard in virgl_video_init() and fix five additional
Intel iHD / xe blockers that were hidden behind it:

  1. picture_width/height_in_mbs_minus1 left as commented-out stubs.
  2. h264 encode sequence params (intra_period, ip_period, picture size,
     chroma_format_idc, frame_mbs_only_flag, direct_8x8_inference_flag,
     log2_max_frame_num_minus4) left as stubs.
  3. Encoder reference surfaces created with NV21 instead of NV12.
  4. vaCreateSurfaces() called without VASurfaceAttribUsageHint.
  5. VAEntrypointEncSliceLP absent from is_supported() and entrypoint map.

No new build options are introduced; non-Mesa drivers are enabled
whenever virglrenderer is built with -Dvideo=true.

Signed-off-by: virglrenderer patch <virglrenderer@patch>
---
 src/vrend/virgl_video.h  |  47 ++++++++++++
 src/vrend/virgl_video.c  | 228 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++----
 2 files changed, 256 insertions(+), 19 deletions(-)

--- a/src/vrend/virgl_video.h
+++ b/src/vrend/virgl_video.h
